What is flatMap()?

flatMap() is used when each element contains a collection, and you want a single flattened stream.

Example
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class FlatMapExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        List<List<String>> departments = Arrays.asList(
                Arrays.asList("Sunil", "Ravi"),
                Arrays.asList("John", "David")
        );

        departments.stream()
                .flatMap(List::stream)
                .forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}
Output
Sunil
Ravi
John
David
Interview Question: map() vs flatMap()
Using map()
List<List<String>> list = Arrays.asList(
        Arrays.asList("A", "B"),
        Arrays.asList("C", "D"));

list.stream()
    .map(x -> x)
    .forEach(System.out::println);

Output:

[A, B]
[C, D]

Using flatMap()
....
list.stream()
    .flatMap(List::stream)
    .forEach(System.out::println);

Output:

A
B
C
D
One-Line Interview Answer
filter() → Select elements.
map() → Transform elements.
flatMap() → Transform and flatten nested collections into a single stream.




