Collectors in Java 8

Collectors is a utility class in the java.util.stream.Collectors package used to collect Stream results into collections, maps, strings, grouping, partitioning, etc.

import java.util.stream.Collectors;
1. Collect to List
List<String> names =
        Arrays.asList("Sunil", "Ravi", "Raj");

List<String> result =
        names.stream()
             .filter(name -> name.startsWith("R"))
             .collect(Collectors.toList());

System.out.println(result);
Output
[Ravi, Raj]
2. Collect to Set
List<Integer> nums =
        Arrays.asList(1,2,2,3,3,4);

Set<Integer> result =
        nums.stream()
            .collect(Collectors.toSet());

System.out.println(result);
Output
[1, 2, 3, 4]
3. joining()

Convert stream elements into a single String.

List<String> names =
        Arrays.asList("Java","Spring","React");

String result =
        names.stream()
             .collect(Collectors.joining(","));

System.out.println(result);
Output
Java,Spring,React
4. counting()

Count elements.

long count =
        names.stream()
             .collect(Collectors.counting());

System.out.println(count);
Output
3
